{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":595,"text":"Radical openness is still a distant future"},{"time":3715,"text":"in the field of school education."},{"time":6011,"text":"We have such a hard time figuring out"},{"time":7900,"text":"that learning is not a place but an activity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12121,"text":"But I want to tell you the story of PISA,"},{"time":15592,"text":"OECD's test to measure the knowledge and skills"},{"time":17970,"text":"of 15-year-olds around the world,"},{"time":19599,"text":"and it's really a story of how international comparisons"},{"time":24121,"text":"have globalized the field of education that we usually treat"},{"time":27396,"text":"as an affair of domestic policy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30331,"text":"Look at how the world looked in the 1960s,"},{"time":32755,"text":"in terms of the proportion of people"},{"time":34586,"text":"who had completed high school."},{"time":37326,"text":"You can see the United States ahead of everyone else,"},{"time":41146,"text":"and much of the economic success of the United States"},{"time":43859,"text":"draws on its long-standing advantage"},{"time":46603,"text":"as the first mover in education."},{"time":49475,"text":"But in the 1970s, some countries caught up."},{"time":52698,"text":"In the 1980s, the global expansion"},{"time":55387,"text":"of the talent pool continued."},{"time":57983,"text":"And the world didn't stop in the 1990s."},{"time":61683,"text":"So in the '60s, the U.S. was first."},{"time":63707,"text":"In the '90s, it was 13th,"},{"time":66643,"text":"and not because standards had fallen,"},{"time":69044,"text":"but because they had risen so much faster elsewhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72799,"text":"Korea shows you what's possible in education."},{"time":76329,"text":"Two generations ago, Korea had the standard of living"},{"time":79274,"text":"of Afghanistan today,"},{"time":81705,"text":"and was one of the lowest education performers."},{"time":85846,"text":"Today, every young Korean finishes high school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91398,"text":"So this tells us that, in a global economy,"},{"time":94374,"text":"it is no longer national improvement that's the benchmark for success,"},{"time":98955,"text":"but the best performing education systems internationally."},{"time":104136,"text":"The trouble is that"},{"time":106579,"text":"measuring how much time people spend in school"},{"time":108449,"text":"or what degree they have got is not always"},{"time":110473,"text":"a good way of seeing what they can actually do."},{"time":115497,"text":"Look at the toxic mix of unemployed graduates on our streets,"},{"time":119170,"text":"while employers say they cannot find the people"},{"time":121364,"text":"with the skills they need."},{"time":125163,"text":"And that tells you that better degrees don't automatically translate"},{"time":128827,"text":"into better skills and better jobs and better lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133197,"text":"So with PISA, we try to change this"},{"time":135806,"text":"by measuring the knowledge and skills"},{"time":137677,"text":"of people directly."},{"time":141113,"text":"And we took a very special angle to this."},{"time":143011,"text":"We were less interested in whether students can simply"},{"time":145493,"text":"reproduce what they have learned in school,"},{"time":148594,"text":"but we wanted to test whether they can extrapolate"},{"time":151310,"text":"from what they know"},{"time":153223,"text":"and apply their knowledge in novel situations."},{"time":157102,"text":"Now, some people have criticized us for this."},{"time":159934,"text":"They say, you know, such a way of measuring outcomes"},{"time":161881,"text":"is terribly unfair to people, because we test students"},{"time":164693,"text":"with problems they haven't seen before."},{"time":167666,"text":"But if you take that logic, you know,"},{"time":169707,"text":"you should consider life unfair, because"},{"time":172635,"text":"the test of truth in life is not whether we can remember"},{"time":175824,"text":"what we learned in school,"},{"time":176944,"text":"but whether we are prepared for change,"},{"time":180265,"text":"whether we are prepared for jobs that haven't been created,"},{"time":182686,"text":"to use technologies that haven't been invented,"},{"time":185032,"text":"to solve problems we just can't anticipate today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189949,"text":"And once hotly contested,"},{"time":192134,"text":"our way of measuring outcomes has actually quickly become the standard."},{"time":195571,"text":"In our latest assessment in 2009,"},{"time":197813,"text":"we measured 74 school systems"},{"time":201225,"text":"that together cover 87 percent of the economy."},{"time":204812,"text":"This chart shows you the performance of countries."},{"time":208486,"text":"In red, sort of below OECD average."},{"time":211373,"text":"Yellow is so-so, and in green are the countries doing really well."},{"time":214749,"text":"You can see Shanghai, Korea, Singapore in Asia;"},{"time":219103,"text":"Finland in Europe;"},{"time":220793,"text":"Canada in North America doing really well."},{"time":225159,"text":"You can also see that there is a gap of almost"},{"time":227600,"text":"three and a half school years between"},{"time":229677,"text":"15-year-olds in Shanghai and 15-year-olds in Chile,"},{"time":233045,"text":"and the gap grows to seven school years"},{"time":235750,"text":"when you include the countries with really poor performance."},{"time":239373,"text":"There's a world of difference in the way in which"},{"time":241844,"text":"young people are prepared for today's economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247046,"text":"But I want to introduce a second important dimension"},{"time":250592,"text":"into this picture."},{"time":252813,"text":"Educators like to talk about equity."},{"time":257188,"text":"With PISA, we wanted to measure how they actually deliver equity,"},{"time":260898,"text":"in terms of ensuring that people"},{"time":263125,"text":"from different social backgrounds have equal chances."},{"time":266565,"text":"And we see that in some countries, the impact"},{"time":268300,"text":"of social background on learning outcomes"},{"time":270179,"text":"is very, very strong."},{"time":271317,"text":"Opportunities are unequally distributed."},{"time":274235,"text":"A lot of potential of young children is wasted."},{"time":277850,"text":"We see in other countries that it matters much less"},{"time":280918,"text":"into which social context you're born."},{"time":284411,"text":"We all want to be there, in the upper right quadrant,"},{"time":286806,"text":"where performance is strong and learning opportunities are equally distributed."},{"time":291302,"text":"Nobody, and no country, can afford to be there,"},{"time":293973,"text":"where performance is poor"},{"time":295354,"text":"and there are large social disparities."},{"time":298699,"text":"And then we can debate, you know, is it better"},{"time":300854,"text":"to be there, where performance is strong"},{"time":302653,"text":"at the price of large disparities?"},{"time":305613,"text":"Or do we want to focus on equity and accept mediocrity?"},{"time":311232,"text":"But actually, if you look at how countries come out on this picture,"},{"time":314214,"text":"you see there are a lot of countries that actually"},{"time":316957,"text":"are combining excellence with equity."},{"time":321725,"text":"In fact, one of the most important lessons from this comparison"},{"time":324333,"text":"is that you don't have to compromise equity"},{"time":327439,"text":"to achieve excellence."},{"time":330286,"text":"These countries have moved on from providing excellence"},{"time":332725,"text":"for just some to providing excellence for all,"},{"time":335994,"text":"a very important lesson."},{"time":337966,"text":"And that also challenges the paradigms of many school systems"},{"time":342942,"text":"that believe they are mainly there to sort people."},{"time":347245,"text":"And ever since those results came out, policymakers,"},{"time":349757,"text":"educators, researchers from around the world"},{"time":351734,"text":"have tried to figure out"},{"time":353095,"text":"what's behind the success of those systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356525,"text":"But let's step back for a moment"},{"time":358349,"text":"and focus on the countries that actually started PISA,"},{"time":361363,"text":"and I'm giving them a colored bubble now."},{"time":363909,"text":"And I'm making the size of the bubble"},{"time":367401,"text":"proportional"},{"time":368943,"text":"to the amount of money that countries spent on students."},{"time":372738,"text":"If money would tell you everything"},{"time":374290,"text":"about the quality of learning outcomes,"},{"time":376369,"text":"you would find all the large bubbles at the top, no?"},{"time":379700,"text":"But that's not what you see."},{"time":382245,"text":"Spending per student only explains about,"},{"time":384550,"text":"well, less than 20 percent"},{"time":386846,"text":"of the performance variation among countries,"},{"time":390364,"text":"and Luxembourg, for example, the most expensive system,"},{"time":392654,"text":"doesn't do particularly well."},{"time":395118,"text":"What you see is that two countries with similar spending"},{"time":397494,"text":"achieve very different results."},{"time":399414,"text":"You also see -- and I think that's one of the most encouraging findings --"},{"time":403663,"text":"that we no longer live in a world that is neatly divided"},{"time":407252,"text":"between rich and well-educated countries,"},{"time":409942,"text":"and poor and badly-educated ones,"},{"time":412262,"text":"a very, very important lesson."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415857,"text":"Let's look at this in greater detail."},{"time":418439,"text":"The red dot shows you"},{"time":420245,"text":"spending per student relative to a country's wealth."},{"time":424702,"text":"One way you can spend money is by paying teachers well,"},{"time":427509,"text":"and you can see Korea investing a lot"},{"time":430014,"text":"in attracting the best people into the teaching profession."},{"time":433038,"text":"And Korea also invests into long school days,"},{"time":434964,"text":"which drives up costs further."},{"time":437720,"text":"Last but not least, Koreans want their teachers"},{"time":439860,"text":"not only to teach but also to develop."},{"time":442140,"text":"They invest in professional development and collaboration"},{"time":444475,"text":"and many other things."},{"time":446555,"text":"All that costs money."},{"time":448196,"text":"How can Korea afford all of this?"},{"time":450866,"text":"The answer is, students in Korea learn in large classes."},{"time":454606,"text":"This is the blue bar which is driving costs down."},{"time":459074,"text":"You go to the next country on the list, Luxembourg,"},{"time":461969,"text":"and you can see the red dot is exactly where it is for Korea,"},{"time":465072,"text":"so Luxembourg spends the same per student as Korea does."},{"time":468605,"text":"But, you know, parents and teachers and policymakers"},{"time":471499,"text":"in Luxembourg all like small classes."},{"time":473946,"text":"You know, it's very pleasant to walk into a small class."},{"time":476714,"text":"So they have invested all their money into there,"},{"time":478618,"text":"and the blue bar, class size, is driving costs up."},{"time":481964,"text":"But even Luxembourg can spend its money only once,"},{"time":486125,"text":"and the price for this is that"},{"time":488330,"text":"teachers are not paid particularly well."},{"time":490434,"text":"Students don't have long hours of learning."},{"time":493113,"text":"And basically, teachers have little time to do anything else than teaching."},{"time":496355,"text":"So you can see two countries spent their money very differently,"},{"time":500036,"text":"and actually how they spent their money"},{"time":502356,"text":"matters a lot more than how much they invest in education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508359,"text":"Let's go back to the year 2000."},{"time":510913,"text":"Remember, that was the year before the iPod was invented."},{"time":514908,"text":"This is how the world looked then"},{"time":517032,"text":"in terms of PISA performance."},{"time":521293,"text":"The first thing you can see is that the bubbles were a lot smaller, no?"},{"time":524108,"text":"We spent a lot less on education,"},{"time":525739,"text":"about 35 percent less on education."},{"time":527811,"text":"So you ask yourself, if education has become so much more expensive,"},{"time":531556,"text":"has it become so much better?"},{"time":534909,"text":"And the bitter truth really is that, you know,"},{"time":537908,"text":"not in many countries."},{"time":540353,"text":"But there are some countries which have seen"},{"time":542436,"text":"impressive improvements."},{"time":545384,"text":"Germany, my own country, in the year 2000,"},{"time":549180,"text":"featured in the lower quadrant,"},{"time":551068,"text":"below average performance, large social disparities."},{"time":554233,"text":"And remember, Germany, we used to be one of those countries"},{"time":556236,"text":"that comes out very well when you just count people who have degrees."},{"time":559964,"text":"Very disappointing results."},{"time":561725,"text":"People were stunned by the results."},{"time":564462,"text":"And for the very first time, the public debate in Germany"},{"time":568253,"text":"was dominated for months by education,"},{"time":571959,"text":"not tax, not other kinds of issues, but education"},{"time":574693,"text":"was the center of the public debate."},{"time":577244,"text":"And then policymakers began to respond to this."},{"time":580463,"text":"The federal government dramatically raised its investment in education."},{"time":584693,"text":"A lot was done to increase the life chances of students"},{"time":588322,"text":"with an immigrant background or from social disadvantage."},{"time":591284,"text":"And what's really interesting is that this wasn't just about"},{"time":595792,"text":"optimizing existing policies,"},{"time":599551,"text":"but data transformed some of the beliefs and paradigms"},{"time":602964,"text":"underlying German education."},{"time":604751,"text":"For example, traditionally, the education of the very young children"},{"time":608637,"text":"was seen as the business of families, and you would have cases"},{"time":611255,"text":"where women were seen as neglecting their family responsibilities"},{"time":614287,"text":"when they sent their children to kindergarten."},{"time":617375,"text":"PISA has transformed that debate,"},{"time":620023,"text":"and pushed early childhood education right at the center"},{"time":622796,"text":"of public policy in Germany."},{"time":625188,"text":"Or traditionally, the German education divides children"},{"time":628889,"text":"at the age of 10, very young children,"},{"time":631637,"text":"between those deemed to pursue careers of knowledge workers"},{"time":635826,"text":"and those who would end up working for the knowledge workers,"},{"time":639176,"text":"and that mainly along socioeconomic lines,"},{"time":641652,"text":"and that paradigm is being challenged now too."},{"time":645820,"text":"A lot of change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648304,"text":"And the good news is, nine years later,"},{"time":651258,"text":"you can see improvements in quality and equity."},{"time":654357,"text":"People have taken up the challenge, done something about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":656633,"text":"Or take Korea, at the other end of the spectrum."},{"time":658761,"text":"In the year 2000, Korea did already very well,"},{"time":661306,"text":"but the Koreans were concerned that only a small share"},{"time":664631,"text":"of their students achieved the really high levels of excellence."},{"time":668990,"text":"They took up the challenge,"},{"time":670804,"text":"and Korea was able to double the proportion of students"},{"time":674338,"text":"achieving excellence in one decade in the field of reading."},{"time":678740,"text":"Well, if you only focus on your brightest students,"},{"time":681293,"text":"you know what happens is disparities grow,"},{"time":683212,"text":"and you can see this bubble moving slightly to the other direction,"},{"time":687012,"text":"but still, an impressive improvement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689723,"text":"A major overhaul of Poland's education"},{"time":692309,"text":"helped to dramatically reduce between variability among schools,"},{"time":695942,"text":"turn around many of the lowest-performing schools,"},{"time":698636,"text":"and raise performance by over half a school year."},{"time":703470,"text":"And you can see other countries as well."},{"time":705261,"text":"Portugal was able to consolidate its fragmented school system,"},{"time":708204,"text":"raise quality and improve equity,"},{"time":711196,"text":"and so did Hungary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713072,"text":"So what you can actually see, there's been a lot of change."},{"time":716503,"text":"And even those people who complain and say that"},{"time":719436,"text":"the relative standing of countries"},{"time":721125,"text":"on something like PISA is just an artifact of culture,"},{"time":724547,"text":"of economic factors, of social issues,"},{"time":727589,"text":"of homogeneity of societies, and so on,"},{"time":730651,"text":"these people must now concede that education improvement is possible."},{"time":735493,"text":"You know, Poland hasn't changed its culture."},{"time":738533,"text":"It didn't change its economy. It didn't change"},{"time":741037,"text":"the compositions of its population."},{"time":743129,"text":"It didn't fire its teachers. It changed its education policies"},{"time":745983,"text":"and practice. Very impressive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748623,"text":"And all that raises, of course, the question: What can we learn"},{"time":751588,"text":"from those countries in the green quadrant"},{"time":753692,"text":"who have achieved high levels of equity,"},{"time":755967,"text":"high levels of performance, and raised outcomes?"},{"time":759699,"text":"And, of course, the question is, can what works in one context"},{"time":763613,"text":"provide a model elsewhere?"},{"time":766329,"text":"Of course, you can't copy and paste education systems wholesale,"},{"time":769659,"text":"but these comparisons have identified a range of factors"},{"time":773586,"text":"that high-performing systems share."},{"time":776907,"text":"Everybody agrees that education is important."},{"time":779467,"text":"Everybody says that."},{"time":781454,"text":"But the test of truth is, how do you weigh that priority"},{"time":784709,"text":"against other priorities?"},{"time":787005,"text":"How do countries pay their teachers"},{"time":789018,"text":"relative to other highly skilled workers?"},{"time":792123,"text":"Would you want your child to become a teacher"},{"time":794608,"text":"rather than a lawyer?"},{"time":796720,"text":"How do the media talk about schools and teachers?"},{"time":798722,"text":"Those are the critical questions, and what we have learned"},{"time":801227,"text":"from PISA is that, in high-performing education systems,"},{"time":805321,"text":"the leaders have convinced their citizens to make choices"},{"time":808871,"text":"that value education, their future,"},{"time":811249,"text":"more than consumption today."},{"time":813921,"text":"And you know what's interesting? You won't believe it,"},{"time":815967,"text":"but there are countries in which the most attractive place"},{"time":818953,"text":"to be is not the shopping center but the school."},{"time":821873,"text":"Those things really exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824140,"text":"But placing a high value on education"},{"time":826113,"text":"is just part of the picture."},{"time":828964,"text":"The other part is the belief that all children"},{"time":831993,"text":"are capable of success."},{"time":835428,"text":"You have some countries where students"},{"time":837189,"text":"are segregated early in their ages."},{"time":839428,"text":"You know, students are divided up,"},{"time":841474,"text":"reflecting the belief that only some children"},{"time":843809,"text":"can achieve world-class standards."},{"time":847361,"text":"But usually that is linked to very strong social disparities."},{"time":851416,"text":"If you go to Japan in Asia, or Finland in Europe,"},{"time":854800,"text":"parents and teachers in those countries"},{"time":856906,"text":"expect every student to succeed,"},{"time":860817,"text":"and you can see that actually mirrored in student behavior."},{"time":864309,"text":"When we asked students what counts"},{"time":867025,"text":"for success in mathematics,"},{"time":869761,"text":"students in North America would typically tell us,"},{"time":872153,"text":"you know, it's all about talent."},{"time":873699,"text":"If I'm not born as a genius in math, I'd better study something else."},{"time":878325,"text":"Nine out of 10 Japanese students say"},{"time":881051,"text":"that it depends on my own investment, on my own effort,"},{"time":885297,"text":"and that tells you a lot about the system that is around them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":890032,"text":"In the past, different students were taught in similar ways."},{"time":894841,"text":"High performers on PISA embrace diversity"},{"time":898173,"text":"with differentiated pedagogical practices."},{"time":901921,"text":"They realize that"},{"time":903897,"text":"ordinary students have extraordinary talents,"},{"time":907041,"text":"and they personalize learning opportunities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910401,"text":"High-performing systems also share"},{"time":912437,"text":"clear and ambitious standards across the entire spectrum."},{"time":916043,"text":"Every student knows what matters."},{"time":918245,"text":"Every student knows what's required to be successful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922332,"text":"And nowhere does the quality of an education system"},{"time":925197,"text":"exceed the quality of its teachers."},{"time":927640,"text":"High-performing systems are very careful"},{"time":930708,"text":"in how they recruit and select their teachers"},{"time":932842,"text":"and how they train them."},{"time":934563,"text":"They watch how they improve the performances of teachers"},{"time":937393,"text":"in difficulties who are struggling,"},{"time":939713,"text":"and how they structure teacher pay."},{"time":942622,"text":"They provide an environment also in which teachers work together"},{"time":946318,"text":"to frame good practice."},{"time":949875,"text":"And they provide intelligent pathways for teachers to grow"},{"time":954036,"text":"in their careers."},{"time":956151,"text":"In bureaucratic school systems,"},{"time":957775,"text":"teachers are often left alone in classrooms"},{"time":959768,"text":"with a lot of prescription on what they should be teaching."},{"time":962935,"text":"High-performing systems are very clear what good performance is."},{"time":966145,"text":"They set very ambitious standards, but then they enable"},{"time":968919,"text":"their teachers to figure out,"},{"time":970696,"text":"what do I need to teach to my students today?"},{"time":974811,"text":"The past was about delivered wisdom in education."},{"time":979357,"text":"Now the challenge is to enable user-generated wisdom."},{"time":984599,"text":"High performers have moved on from professional"},{"time":988239,"text":"or from administrative forms of accountability and control --"},{"time":991903,"text":"sort of, how do you check whether people do what they're supposed to do in education --"},{"time":995140,"text":"to professional forms of work organization."},{"time":998806,"text":"They enable their teachers to make innovations in pedagogy."},{"time":1002678,"text":"They provide them with the kind of development they need"},{"time":1005168,"text":"to develop stronger pedagogical practices."},{"time":1009230,"text":"The goal of the past was standardization and compliance."},{"time":1014888,"text":"High-performing systems have made teachers"},{"time":1017622,"text":"and school principals inventive."},{"time":1020908,"text":"In the past, the policy focus was on outcomes,"},{"time":1023607,"text":"on provision."},{"time":1025789,"text":"The high-performing systems have helped teachers"},{"time":1028592,"text":"and school principals to look outwards to the next teacher,"},{"time":1031033,"text":"the next school around their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1033726,"text":"And the most impressive outcomes of world-class systems"},{"time":1035892,"text":"is that they achieve high performance across the entire system."},{"time":1039039,"text":"You've seen Finland doing so well on PISA,"},{"time":1041236,"text":"but what makes Finland so impressive"},{"time":1042926,"text":"is that only five percent of the performance variation"},{"time":1046903,"text":"amongst students lies between schools."},{"time":1049359,"text":"Every school succeeds."},{"time":1051675,"text":"This is where success is systemic."},{"time":1054406,"text":"And how do they do that?"},{"time":1056110,"text":"They invest resources where they can make the most difference."},{"time":1058802,"text":"They attract the strongest principals into the toughest schools,"},{"time":1063910,"text":"and the most talented teachers"},{"time":1066118,"text":"into the most challenging classroom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1068061,"text":"Last but not least, those countries align policies"},{"time":1071190,"text":"across all areas of public policy."},{"time":1073410,"text":"They make them coherent over sustained periods of time,"},{"time":1076543,"text":"and they ensure that what they do is consistently implemented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1081246,"text":"Now, knowing what successful systems are doing"},{"time":1083550,"text":"doesn't yet tell us how to improve."},{"time":1086341,"text":"That's also clear, and that's where some of the limits"},{"time":1088799,"text":"of international comparisons of PISA are."},{"time":1092274,"text":"That's where other forms of research need to kick in,"},{"time":1094977,"text":"and that's also why PISA doesn't venture into"},{"time":1097435,"text":"telling countries what they should be doing."},{"time":1099195,"text":"But its strength lies in telling them"},{"time":1101018,"text":"what everybody else has been doing."},{"time":1103773,"text":"And the example of PISA shows that data"},{"time":1105969,"text":"can be more powerful than administrative control of financial subsidy"},{"time":1109287,"text":"through which we usually run education systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1113228,"text":"You know, some people argue that"},{"time":1116266,"text":"changing educational administration"},{"time":1118454,"text":"is like moving graveyards."},{"time":1120895,"text":"You just can't rely on the people out there to help you with this. (Laughter)"},{"time":1125782,"text":"But PISA has shown what's possible in education."},{"time":1130649,"text":"It has helped countries to see that improvement is possible."},{"time":1134454,"text":"It has taken away excuses from those who are complacent."},{"time":1138662,"text":"And it has helped countries to set meaningful targets"},{"time":1142095,"text":"in terms of measurable goals achieved by the world's leaders."},{"time":1145193,"text":"If we can help every child, every teacher, every school,"},{"time":1149743,"text":"every principal, every parent see what improvement is possible,"},{"time":1153398,"text":"that only the sky is the limit to education improvement,"},{"time":1156134,"text":"we have laid the foundations"},{"time":1158030,"text":"for better policies and better lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1160213,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1162746,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}